102
00:07:14,291 --> 00:07:16,384
Think I'm hot,
do you?

103
00:07:16,493 --> 00:07:20,452
Hmm. Lukewarm. Just above
room temperature.

104
00:07:20,564 --> 00:07:22,725
Well, what the hell
am I then?

105
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:24,801
Whatever he is,
it's clearly tied to this amulet.

106
00:07:24,902 --> 00:07:28,463
<i>Spike's essence,</i>
<i>for lack of a better term...</i>

107
00:07:28,572 --> 00:07:30,472
must've been
held within it.

108
00:07:30,574 --> 00:07:33,168
<i>Do you have any memory</i>
<i>of a strange sensation...</i>

109
00:07:33,277 --> 00:07:35,177
when it released
its energy?

110
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:37,839
What, you mean my skin and muscle
burning away from the bone?

111
00:07:37,948 --> 00:07:39,677
<i>Organs exploding</i>
<i>in my chest?</i>

112
00:07:39,783 --> 00:07:42,877
Eyeballs melting in their sockets?
No. No memory at all. Thanks for asking.

113
00:07:42,986 --> 00:07:44,886
<i>[Angel]</i>
<i>Okay, he's connected to the amulet.</i>

114
00:07:44,988 --> 00:07:49,357
Last I heard, it was buried deep inside
of the Hellmouth. How did it end up here?

115
00:07:49,459 --> 00:07:54,692
Maybe he's here for a reason. You know, some
higher purpose or something he's destined for...

116
00:07:54,798 --> 00:07:57,232
sent to us by the Powers
That Be to help us or...

117
00:07:57,334 --> 00:07:59,996
Who gave them
the bloody right to do that?

118
00:08:00,103 --> 00:08:01,934
[Scoffs]

119
00:08:02,039 --> 00:08:07,409
Can't a man die in peace without some
high almighty deciding it's not his time?

120
00:08:07,511 --> 00:08:09,376
Let's have a little
more fun with him, eh?

121
00:08:09,479 --> 00:08:13,575
<i>You'd think that saving the soddin'world</i>
<i>would be enough to earn me a rest.</i>

122
00:08:13,684 --> 00:08:15,845
- You'd think.
- Spike...

123
00:08:17,020 --> 00:08:20,717
Hmm?
Oh, balls.

124
00:08:25,028 --> 00:08:28,964
- Now what?
- I don't know. He just...

125
00:08:29,066 --> 00:08:31,193
What did he mean,
saving the world?

126
00:08:32,169 --> 00:08:34,933
Oh, that?
Well...

127
00:08:35,038 --> 00:08:37,563
[Scoffs] Buffy did most
of the work.

128
00:08:37,674 --> 00:08:39,904
Well, he helped, but...

129
00:08:40,010 --> 00:08:43,912
Hmm?
What? What?

130
00:08:44,014 --> 00:08:46,744
- Took the whats right out of our mouths.
- Where'd you go?

131
00:08:48,418 --> 00:08:52,912
- Don't you know?
- I'm... I was...

132
00:08:54,258 --> 00:08:57,557
You. This is your fault.

133
00:08:57,661 --> 00:09:00,721
- Mine?
- You brought that bloody amulet to Sunnydale.

134
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:03,629
<i>You would have been the one to use it,</i>
<i>until you chickened out.</i>

135
00:09:03,734 --> 00:09:05,565
- What did you...
- You heard me.

136
00:09:05,669 --> 00:09:08,502
<i>You left town in the nick of time,</i>
<i>before the death and mayhem.</i>

137
00:09:08,605 --> 00:09:10,766
Abandoned the woman
you claimed to love.

138
00:09:10,874 --> 00:09:12,739
She made the call.
It wasn't my choice.

139
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:15,812
And this bloody hell
wasn't mine.

140
00:09:15,913 --> 00:09:19,405
<i>I'm not you. I don't give a piss</i>
<i>about atonement or destiny.</i>

141
00:09:19,516 --> 00:09:23,145
Just because I've got me a soul doesn't mean
I'm gonna let myself be led around...

142
00:09:23,253 --> 00:09:26,654
- Excuse me?
- Did... Did you just say...

143
00:09:27,758 --> 00:09:30,818
Spike has a soul?
You never said.

144
00:09:30,928 --> 00:09:34,329
- Didn't seem worth mentioning.
- Seems to be a lot of that.

145
00:09:34,431 --> 00:09:39,698
Or maybe Captain Forehead
was feeling a little less special.

146
00:09:39,803 --> 00:09:42,829
<i>Didn't like me crashing</i>
<i>his exclusive club.</i>

147
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:45,272
Another vampire
with a soul in the world.

148
00:09:46,443 --> 00:09:50,641
You're not <i>in</i> the world, Casper.

149
00:10:05,395 --> 00:10:08,159
Runnin' away again?

150
00:10:08,265 --> 00:10:11,200
Nice new M.O.
I can see why heroes like you...

151
00:10:11,301 --> 00:10:13,292
get rewarded with
the shiny new glass and chrome.

152
00:10:13,403 --> 00:10:16,497
