you advise him that he's no longer our client.

223
00:14:13,243 --> 00:14:16,269
- Me?
- You got it, counselor.

224
00:14:16,379 --> 00:14:18,847
- You tell Mr<i>...</i> [Clear Throat]
- Hainsley.

225
00:14:18,949 --> 00:14:21,679
Hainsley that
Wolfram and Hart...

226
00:14:21,785 --> 00:14:25,118
is under new management and out of
the grave-robbing business.

227
00:14:25,222 --> 00:14:28,419
Now, run along
and go argue your case.

228
00:14:28,525 --> 00:14:31,926
- Me?
- Go.

229
00:14:34,998 --> 00:14:37,466
You don't have to
take that from him, mate.

230
00:14:37,567 --> 00:14:39,592
Stay out of this, Spike.
You don't work here.

231
00:14:39,703 --> 00:14:42,570
Damn right I don't.
Look at you.

232
00:14:42,672 --> 00:14:46,574
<i>This is what you do now? Delegate</i>
<i>the dirty work to spineless, low-level flunkies?</i>

233
00:14:46,676 --> 00:14:48,576
No offense.

234
00:14:48,678 --> 00:14:53,206
<i>The mighty hero, reduced to</i>
<i>a bloody bureaucrat.</i>

235
00:14:53,316 --> 00:14:55,284
If a certain Slayer
could see you now...

236
00:14:55,385 --> 00:14:57,785
Get outta here, Spike.

237
00:14:57,887 --> 00:15:01,823
Gladly. Cruel enough punishment
being stuck here as a spook...

238
00:15:01,925 --> 00:15:04,723
while you play
chairman of the boring.

239
00:15:04,828 --> 00:15:08,059
But hell if I'm going to spend
my afterlife in your stinking city.

240
00:15:08,164 --> 00:15:10,257
Get stuffed.

241
00:15:28,752 --> 00:15:32,279
<i>You don't think</i>
<i>he's really gone, do you?</i>

242
00:15:32,389 --> 00:15:35,483
That what's
on your mind?

243
00:15:35,592 --> 00:15:37,526
Could've been me, Wes.

244
00:15:37,627 --> 00:15:39,618
It was supposed to be me.

245
00:15:39,729 --> 00:15:42,391
- You're not feeling guilty.
- What, about Spike?

246
00:15:42,499 --> 00:15:44,626
[Chuckles]
That's... That's not...

247
00:15:47,637 --> 00:15:51,368
Wolfram and Hart
gave me the amulet.

248
00:15:51,474 --> 00:15:53,874
They must have
expected me to use it...

249
00:15:53,977 --> 00:15:57,310
and they had to have known it would have
done to me what it did to Spike, so...

250
00:15:57,414 --> 00:15:59,905
<i>Why bother handing you</i>
<i>the keys to the kingdom?</i>

251
00:16:00,016 --> 00:16:03,543
<i>It doesn't make sense. What are</i>
<i>the senior partners playing at?</i>

252
00:16:03,653 --> 00:16:05,883
Maybe there's dissent
in their ranks. Or maybe...

253
00:16:05,989 --> 00:16:09,356
there's another player in the game
they and we don't know anything about.

254
00:16:11,094 --> 00:16:13,654
Then again, maybe they got exactly
what they were after.

255
00:16:15,799 --> 00:16:17,699
- Spike.
- He may be the one they...

256
00:16:17,801 --> 00:16:20,395
What are you doin' here?
I thought you left town.

257
00:16:20,503 --> 00:16:22,562
Don't think
I didn't bleeding try.

258
00:16:22,672 --> 00:16:26,403
Every time I got as far as the city limits,
I kept popping back here.

259
00:16:26,509 --> 00:16:29,103
Like my insides
were getting yanked.

260
00:16:29,212 --> 00:16:32,409
<i>I suspected as much. The amulet's</i>
<i>Wolfram and Hart's property.</i>

261
00:16:32,515 --> 00:16:35,177
It's bound to this place.
And since Spike's connected to it...

262
00:16:35,285 --> 00:16:38,186
Hey, I'm nobody's
bloody property, Percy.

263
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:43,248
<i>So what, I'm just stuck here forever?</i>
<i>I bet you're loving this, aren't you?</i>

264
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:45,692
Knowing you'll be haunting me
till the end of time.

265
00:16:45,795 --> 00:16:47,888
Mm, it's a dream come true.

266
00:16:47,997 --> 00:16:52,457
<i>[Harmony] Uh, boss? That Novac lawyer</i>
<i>you sent over to dump the client...</i>

267
00:16:52,569 --> 00:16:54,469
Well, he's back.

268
00:16:54,571 --> 00:16:57,870
- Okay, send him in.
- Okay.

269
00:17:06,683 --> 00:17:08,708
<i>[Angel]</i>
<i>What is...</i>

270
00:17:15,558 --> 00:17:17,890
Hmm. OI' buckets here was right.

271
00:17:17,994 --> 00:17:19,894
You guys are doin'
a bang-up job.

272
00:17:28,338 --> 00:17:30,602
Harmony, get me
Novac's contact list.

273
00:17:30,707 --> 00:17:32,902
Close relations,
next of kin.

274
00:17:33,009 --> 00:17:35,807
And let's be discreet about this
for the time being, okay?

275
00:17:35,912 --> 00:17:41,111
Discreet? Oh, you mean like not tell anyone
about bucket o' lawyer.

276
00:17:41,217 --> 00:17:42,980
- Harmony, contact list.
- Hey.

277
00:17:43,086 --> 00:17:44,986
Got word you wanted the file
on Magnus Hainsley.

278
00:17:45,088 --> 00:17:46,988
Dig this.
He's a sorcerer, big-time.

279
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:48,990
Rich with old money
and older mojo.

280
00:17:49,092 --> 00:17:51,287
Owns a respectable block of shares
in Wolfram and Hart...

281
00:17:51,394 --> 00:17:53,294
and he's connected
up the wazoo.

282
00:17:53,396 --> 00:17:56,661
Carries influence with power players
in the entertainment industry, politics...

283
00:17:56,766 --> 00:17:58,859
- Oh, he's a necromancer.
- Power over the dead.

284
00:17:58,968 --> 00:18:01,869
That explains the bodies
Wolfram and Hart's been providing him.

285
00:18:01,971 --> 00:18:05,099
But not what he's been doing with them.
Out of my chair.

286
00:18:06,342 --> 00:18:09,607
- Make me.
- What's in the buckets?

287
00:18:09,712 --> 00:18:13,512
Your man Novac. Guess he's been...
what do you call it... downsized.

288
00:18:13,616 --> 00:18:16,551
It's a message
from Magnus Hainsley.

289
00:18:16,653 --> 00:18:18,848
And I'm gonna
reply to it personally.

290
00:18:18,955 --> 00:18:22,857
- You can't take Hainsley on.
- I'm not gonna risk him
turning somebody else into chowder.

291
00:18:22,959 --> 00:18:25,655
<i>Angel, you've got a multibillion-dollar</i>
<i>company at your disposal...</i>

292
00:18:25,762 --> 00:18:27,696
<i>with armed</i>
<i>and trained personnel.</i>

293
00:18:27,797 --> 00:18:31,995
- They cramp my style.
<i>- Your style's not going to cut it</i>
<i>with a necromancer.</i>

294
00:18:32,101 --> 00:18:35,969
We should probably avoid
an eye-for-an-eye escalation here.

295
00:18:36,072 --> 00:18:39,872
- I'm not goin' for his eyes, Wes.
- I know what you should go for.

296
00:18:41,077 --> 00:18:44,137
It'll hurt him. Bad.

297
00:18:59,329 --> 00:19:01,524
<i>[Spike]</i>
<i>Knew you'd pick the Viper.</i>

298
00:19:01,631 --> 00:19:05,192
- So bloody predictable.
- Spike, get out of the car.

299
00:19:05,301 --> 00:19:07,895
- No.
- What?

300
00:19:08,004 --> 00:19:11,531
This "haunting you until the end of time" idea
of yours is starting to sound appealing.

301
00:19:11,641 --> 00:19:13,939
<i>I could drive you</i>
<i>completely starkers.</i>

302
00:19:14,043 --> 00:19:18,377
Right out of your gourd. Yeah, and you wouldn't
be able to do a soddin' thing about it.

303
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:32,794
Fancy a road trip?

304
00:19:32,896 --> 00:19:37,128
This'll be fun, eh?
You and me together again.

305
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:39,724
So, where are we off to?

306
00:19:39,836 --> 00:19:42,361
To see the wizard.

307
00:19:50,246 --> 00:19:52,714
Do you have an appointment
with Mr. Hainsley?

308
00:19:52,815 --> 00:19:56,114
Let's just say
he sent us an invitation.

309
00:19:56,219 --> 00:19:59,279
We're... I'm from
Wolfram and Hart.

310
00:20:00,557 --> 00:20:02,525
I'm his date.

311
00:20:02,625 --> 00:20:05,253
<i>Mr. Hainsley is with</i>
<i>a customer at the moment.</i>

312
00:20:05,361 --> 00:20:08,626
I'm afraid he does not suffer
interruption lightly.

313
00:20:08,731 --> 00:20:12,167
I'm not so worried about his suffering.
Go ahead and interrupt.

314
00:20:12,268 --> 00:20:15,601
As you wish.
Please wait here, gentlemen.

315
00:20:18,841 --> 00:20:21,332
Oh, life among
the power elite.

316
00:20:21,444 --> 00:20:23,344
It's all so civilized.

317
00:20:23,446 --> 00:20:26,973
Hainsley grinds up one of your people
into chum, and you drop by for tea.

318
00:20:27,083 --> 00:20:29,381
I'm hopin' to avoid
a body count here.

319
00:20:29,485 --> 00:20:33,854
No worries. Looks like
this Hainsley keeps one on hand.

320
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:46,734
Man likes to play
with dollies.

321
00:20:46,836 --> 00:20:48,861
This isn't for him.

322
00:20:50,206 --> 00:20:52,766
<i>[Classical: Piano]</i>

323
00:20:59,282 --> 00:21:01,250
It's a showroom.

324
00:21:09,826 --> 00:21:12,226
[Droning]

325
00:21:17,433 --> 00:21:19,663
<i>[Man] I thought about</i>
<i>going older with it.</i>

326
00:21:19,769 --> 00:21:22,465
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>More distinguished, kind of...</i>

327
00:21:22,572 --> 00:21:26,235
<i>a 50-something</i>
<i>Shirley Temple Black with it.</i>

328
00:21:26,342 --> 00:21:30,369
<i>You know, that ultrarespectable</i>
<i>ambassador-to-somewhere feel.</i>

329
00:21:31,681 --> 00:21:34,343
But in the end, l...
I went with pretty.

330
00:21:34,450 --> 00:21:36,816
I suppose we all do
in the end, don't we?

331
00:21:36,919 --> 00:21:40,650
You know, in the end, pretty people
just seem to have it so much...

332
00:21:40,757 --> 00:21:42,657
Oh. Whoa.

333
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:45,023
There's something you don't
see every... [Groans]

334
00:21:47,497 --> 00:21:50,557
Mm. Okay, yeah,
that's feelin' a little weird.

335
00:21:54,737 --> 00:21:56,728
<i>Excuse the interruption, sir.</i>

336
00:21:56,839 --> 00:22:01,003
There are some more men from
Wolfram and Hart asking to see you.

337
00:22:01,110 --> 00:22:03,010
They seem
rather adamant.

338
00:22:03,112 --> 00:22:07,014
- Kill them.
- Very good, sir.

339
00:22:07,116 --> 00:22:09,516
<i>[Droning Continues]</i>

340
00:22:12,588 --> 00:22:15,216
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>Maybe the geezer's just lonely.</i>

341
00:22:15,324 --> 00:22:17,349
Throws himself
a surprise party every night.

342
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:20,395
Picks out one of these painted pigeons
and shows her a good time...

343
00:22:20,496 --> 00:22:22,191
if you know
what I mean.

344
00:22:22,298 --> 00:22:24,357
What? I'm sure
they don't mind.

345
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:27,095
- Yeah, I mind.
- Why?

346
00:22:27,203 --> 00:22:30,070
They're the lucky ones, aren't they?
It's over for them.

347
00:22:30,173 --> 00:22:32,903
They've shuffled off,
cleanly, the one time.

348
00:22:33,009 --> 00:22:35,978
Nobody's shoving them back into this
stinking world against their will.

349
00:22:36,079 --> 00:22:37,569
I mind.

350
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:40,148
<i>[Footsteps Approaching]</i>

351
00:22:40,249 --> 00:22:45,778
Mr. Hainsley has asked that I send you
back to Wolfram and Hart, gentlemen.

352
00:22:45,888 --> 00:22:48,584
In a manner of speaking.

353
00:22:49,892 --> 00:22:51,985
Uh-oh. Looks like
it's buckets for you.

354
00:22:55,264 --> 00:22:57,061
[Screams]

355
00:22:58,468 --> 00:23:00,936
A spoon?
That's just...

356
00:23:05,541 --> 00:23:08,135
Well, okay, that's more...

357
00:23:10,379 --> 00:23:12,973
disappointing really.

358
00:23:13,082 --> 00:23:15,983
I know you can't help, but could you
not root for the other team?

359
00:23:16,085 --> 00:23:18,679
I'll root for anyone with half a chance
of taking you down a notch.

360
00:23:18,788 --> 00:23:21,313
- What is your problem?
- You are, you ponce.

361
00:23:21,424 --> 00:23:23,984
You're my problem.
You've got it too good.

362
00:23:24,093 --> 00:23:26,118
You're king
of a 30-floor castle...

363
00:23:26,229 --> 00:23:28,993
with all the cars, comfort, power and glory
you could ever want.

364
00:23:29,098 --> 00:23:32,033
And here I save the world, throw myself
on the proverbial hand grenade...

365
00:23:32,135 --> 00:23:34,968
for love, honor, and all the right reasons,
and what do I get?

366
00:23:35,071 --> 00:23:38,302
Bloody well toasted and ghosted
is what I get, isn't it? It's just not fair.

367
00:23:38,407 --> 00:23:40,841
Fair? You asked
for a soul. I didn't.

368
00:23:40,943 --> 00:23:43,173
It almost killed me.
I spend a hundred years...

369
00:23:43,279 --> 00:23:45,509
trying to come to terms
with infinite remorse.

370
00:23:45,615 --> 00:23:48,675
You spent three weeks moaning
in a basement, and then you were fine.

371
00:23:48,785 --> 00:23:50,480
What's fair about that?

372
00:23:50,586 --> 00:23:52,850
Are you getting blurry,
or is it...

373
00:23:54,957 --> 00:23:56,857
[Groans]

374
00:24:03,466 --> 00:24:06,299
Come in.
It's open.

375
00:24:06,402 --> 00:24:11,032
- Hainsley.
- Didn't know it was the head cheese himself.

376
00:24:11,140 --> 00:24:14,200
Thought for sure
you were another lackey.

377
00:24:14,310 --> 00:24:16,744
You should show more respect.

378
00:24:16,846 --> 00:24:18,746
<i>Oh, uh...</i>
<i>[Chuckles]</i>

379
00:24:18,848 --> 00:24:21,373
I can see you guys
have a... a thing going on.

380
00:24:21,484 --> 00:24:25,352
<i>Don't let me get in your way.</i>
<i>I'll... let myself out.</i>

381
00:24:27,690 --> 00:24:29,920
<i>So how much</i>
<i>do you charge?</i>

382
00:24:30,026 --> 00:24:33,154
Installing the average demon
in a human body.

383
00:24:33,262 --> 00:24:36,095
I'm sure a lot of them
would love to pass as people.

384
00:24:36,199 --> 00:24:38,394
You know,
walk amongst the sheep.

385
00:24:38,501 --> 00:24:42,665
Believe me, friend,
the average demon can't afford it.

386
00:24:42,772 --> 00:24:44,763
I'm cuttin' off
your supply, Hainsley.

387
00:24:44,874 --> 00:24:47,035
<i>As of now,</i>
<i>you're body shop's...</i>

388
00:24:47,143 --> 00:24:48,906
[Straining]

389
00:24:49,011 --> 00:24:51,844
Who do you think
you're talking to?

390
00:24:59,789 --> 00:25:02,815
I eat the dead
for breakfast, son.

391
00:25:02,925 --> 00:25:05,894
And you're just another
plate o' bacon and eggs.

392
00:25:09,999 --> 00:25:11,694
A ghost, huh?

393
00:25:11,801 --> 00:25:14,964
<i>You brought a ghost</i>
<i>as your backup, vampire?</i>

394
00:25:15,071 --> 00:25:18,472
I'm not here to back him up.
I just haunt the bastard.

395
00:25:18,574 --> 00:25:21,737
- Stay out of this.
- Oh, stick it, far as it'll go.

396
00:25:21,844 --> 00:25:24,244
You go ahead, wiz.
Do as you want.

397
00:25:24,347 --> 00:25:27,441
<i>- What I want is to</i>
<i>turn you inside out, like a shirt.</i>
- Ah! Ow!

398
00:25:27,550 --> 00:25:30,075
I could dust you
right now, boy.

399
00:25:30,186 --> 00:25:32,154
Wouldn't even need a stake.

400
00:25:34,090 --> 00:25:39,392
<i>But that would be too big an insult</i>
<i>for the senior partners to overlook.</i>

401
00:25:39,495 --> 00:25:42,123
It seems that
they've got plans for you.

402
00:25:44,033 --> 00:25:46,968
- I've got plans of my own.
<i>- [Phone Beeping]</i>

403
00:25:48,070 --> 00:25:50,834
Gunn. Do it.

404
00:25:50,940 --> 00:25:54,899
And what was that?
Just call in an air strike?

405
00:25:55,011 --> 00:25:56,979
I just froze
all your bank accounts.

406
00:25:57,079 --> 00:25:59,309
<i>Terminated your paper assets,</i>
<i>and turned your books over...</i>

407
00:25:59,415 --> 00:26:02,748
to a very motivated contact
we have at the I.R.S.

408
00:26:02,852 --> 00:26:06,253
<i>Five minutes from now,</i>
<i>you'll have nothing but this house.</i>

409
00:26:06,355 --> 00:26:08,090
<i>Ten minutes from now,</i>
<i>that'll go into foreclosure.</i>

410
00:26:08,090 --> 00:26:09,648
<i>Ten minutes from now,</i>
<i>that'll go into foreclosure.</i>

411
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:12,489
You can't do that.

412
00:26:12,595 --> 00:26:15,359
- I'll let myself out.
- It's not legal.

413
00:26:15,464 --> 00:26:20,299
You think you can get away with that.
[Laughs] I'll sue you to hell.

414
00:26:20,403 --> 00:26:22,837
Good luck.
We're your lawyers.

415
00:26:24,140 --> 00:26:28,133
This isn't over, vampire.

416
00:26:28,277 --> 00:26:30,575
<i>That's how you're gonna fight</i>
<i>evil now? Call the I.R.S.?</i>

417
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:33,240
- Whatever it takes.
- Hello, I.R.S.? Could you fight my battles for me?

418
00:26:33,349 --> 00:26:35,681
While you're at it,
could you wipe my wide, spotty a...

419
00:26:35,785 --> 00:26:37,685
Oh, thank God.

420
00:26:38,888 --> 00:26:40,856
...ss.

421
00:26:43,259 --> 00:26:46,456
- You.
- Power over the dead.

422
00:26:46,562 --> 00:26:48,621
But enough about me.
Let's talk about you.

423
00:26:48,731 --> 00:26:51,029
<i>You're a ghost.</i>

424
00:26:51,133 --> 00:26:53,363
Close enough anyway.

425
00:26:53,469 --> 00:26:55,835
That's just
a horrible way to be.

426
00:26:55,938 --> 00:26:58,805
<i>You're not here,</i>
<i>you're not there.</i>

427
00:26:58,908 --> 00:27:01,138
Just lost somewhere
in the middle.

428
00:27:01,243 --> 00:27:04,679
<i>You can't fight against it.</i>
<i>You can't fix it.</i>

429
00:27:04,780 --> 00:27:07,647
<i>Hell, you can't even lift a finger</i>
<i>'cause you simply don't have any.</i>

430
00:27:07,750 --> 00:27:09,650
Yeah.
What's it to you?

431
00:27:09,752 --> 00:27:13,051
I can give you back
what's been taken from you.

432
00:27:13,155 --> 00:27:16,318
Freedom.
Power of choice.

433
00:27:16,425 --> 00:27:21,192
I can put your destiny back in
your own flesh-and-bone hands.

434
00:27:21,297 --> 00:27:25,393
<i>That's right.</i>
<i>A corporeal body.</i>

435
00:27:25,501 --> 00:27:28,595
I can make that happen.

436
00:27:28,704 --> 00:27:31,901
But to do that, I need you
to do something for me.

437
00:27:32,008 --> 00:27:33,908
Something that
might require...

438
00:27:34,010 --> 00:27:36,205
Hurt Angel? That it?
You want me to hurt Angel?

439
00:27:42,051 --> 00:27:44,519
You've come
to the right ghost.

440
00:27:49,959 --> 00:27:52,223
<i>Wiped out every asset</i>
<i>we could find on Hainsley.</i>

441
00:27:52,328 --> 00:27:55,229
Wasn't easy. Man's got his fingers
in a lot of dirty pies.

442
00:27:55,331 --> 00:27:58,129
I think pies are gonna be off
his menu for a while.

443
00:27:58,234 --> 00:28:00,964
It's gotta hurt. I mean,
damn, who doesn't love pie?

444
00:28:01,070 --> 00:28:03,368
<i>- [Fred] You're back.</i>
- Hainsley out of business?

445
00:28:03,472 --> 00:28:06,236
- Yeah, for the time being.
- So he's not going away?

446
00:28:06,342 --> 00:28:09,334
I think that "This isn't over yet, vampire"
may be the tip-off.

447
00:28:09,445 --> 00:28:12,972
Guys, can we get back
to my, uh, spiritual crisis?

448
00:28:13,082 --> 00:28:15,107
Yes. Spike.

449
00:28:15,217 --> 00:28:16,980
Popped out at me
at Hainsley's place.

450
00:28:17,086 --> 00:28:19,850
But we all know that
he'll be back, and back...

451
00:28:19,955 --> 00:28:22,321
and back, and I really don't want
that happening again.

452
00:28:22,425 --> 00:28:26,054
So explain to me how we're going
to get him out of here.

453
00:28:26,162 --> 00:28:28,255
He can't
get out of here.

454
00:28:28,364 --> 00:28:30,594
Please don't tell me that.

455
00:28:30,699 --> 00:28:32,599
Okay.

456
00:28:32,701 --> 00:28:35,829
Wesley, you tell him.

457
00:28:35,938 --> 00:28:39,396
I've had my entire department doing
thorough research on the amulet.

458
00:28:39,508 --> 00:28:44,639
There's not much. Not in the way
of releasing Spike from it anyway.

459
00:28:44,747 --> 00:28:47,739
At least not in
the conventional sense.

460
00:28:48,851 --> 00:28:50,910
And what's
the unconventional sense?

461
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:53,614
Something he asked for.

462
00:28:53,722 --> 00:28:56,156
Eternal rest.

463
00:29:04,867 --> 00:29:07,427
<i>- Fine. Don't talk to me.</i>
- What?

464
00:29:07,536 --> 00:29:10,699
Whole time we were a thing
you treated me like day-old rat blood.

465
00:29:10,806 --> 00:29:14,799
Why should now be any diff?
Just 'cause you've gone all Patrick Swayze.

466
00:29:14,910 --> 00:29:17,970
- What are you on about?
- Well, gee, nothing much.

467
00:29:18,080 --> 00:29:20,776
Just since you're
all soulful now...

468
00:29:20,883 --> 00:29:25,115
I thought maybe, just maybe,
you might have learned to open up a little.

469
00:29:25,221 --> 00:29:27,815
<i>You know, talk.</i>

470
00:29:27,923 --> 00:29:30,721
But I guess a leopard
can't change his stripes.

471
00:29:30,826 --> 00:29:33,818
Spots, you dink.
Leopards have spots.

472
00:29:33,929 --> 00:29:35,863
Oh, excuse me,
Mr. Brainy.

473
00:29:35,965 --> 00:29:40,061
Thank you so much for sharing.
Wow, what a breakthrough.

474
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,974
<i>[Wesley] Yes, this is</i>
<i>an unusual situation...</i>

475
00:29:47,076 --> 00:29:49,476
<i>but I think it's</i>
<i>our only choice.</i>

476
00:29:49,578 --> 00:29:52,513
<i>It's what we'd do in any case</i>
<i>of a haunting, isn't it?</i>

477
00:29:52,615 --> 00:29:54,810
<i>An exorcism of sorts.</i>

478
00:29:56,652 --> 00:30:00,918
I mean, I know he's already dead,
but he'd be gone dead.

479
00:30:01,023 --> 00:30:03,924
<i>Forever. Itjust</i>
<i>doesn't seem right.</i>

480
00:30:04,026 --> 00:30:06,187
<i>I agree. But neither</i>
<i>is leaving him here.</i>

481
00:30:06,295 --> 00:30:09,423
Trapped between realms,
with no control over his fate...

482
00:30:09,532 --> 00:30:12,160
<i>not able to touch anything,</i>
<i>affect anything.</i>

483
00:30:12,268 --> 00:30:14,168
<i>Unable to fight.</i>

484
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:16,568
Letting him cross over seems
the most merciful thing we...

485
00:30:16,672 --> 00:30:21,507
Yeah, yeah, mercy. You know,
I'm all for it. Just tell me how we do it.

486
00:30:21,610 --> 00:30:24,511
The amulet's protected,
invulnerable to anything.

487
00:30:24,613 --> 00:30:27,582
But the magic that's protecting it
doesn't work on hallowed ground.

488
00:30:27,683 --> 00:30:31,175
- Hallowed? Like a church?
- Or cemetery, yes.

489
00:30:31,287 --> 00:30:34,688
<i>- It has to be taken there and destroyed.</i>
- Destroyed how?

490
00:30:34,790 --> 00:30:37,759
I think a sharp blow
would probably do the trick.

491
00:30:39,395 --> 00:30:41,363
Angel, what do you think?

492
00:30:46,202 --> 00:30:48,568
Think I want
to sleep on it.

493
00:31:50,065 --> 00:31:52,659
<i>[Spike]</i>
<i>Well, look at you.</i>

494
00:31:52,768 --> 00:31:54,759
Oh, no. No.

495
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:56,701
No, no!

496
00:31:56,805 --> 00:31:59,933
Sitting in
luxury's ample lap.

497
00:32:01,644 --> 00:32:04,169
Top of the world...

498
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:06,271
<i>Iooking down on...</i>

499
00:32:06,382 --> 00:32:08,612
well, everyone.

500
00:32:10,219 --> 00:32:12,119
It's good to be king,
isn't it?

501
00:32:12,221 --> 00:32:15,748
Ground rules: Haunt me all you want
during business hours...

502
00:32:15,858 --> 00:32:18,292
but this space...
off-limits.

503
00:32:18,394 --> 00:32:20,692
Relax, beefcake.
I didn't come for a fight.

504
00:32:23,732 --> 00:32:26,895
- Really?
- Not that I could, right?

505
00:32:27,002 --> 00:32:29,129
Can't touch.
Can't affect anything.

506
00:32:31,106 --> 00:32:34,872
Yeah, I overheard your little group
powwow about me.

507
00:32:34,977 --> 00:32:37,844
- How much?
- Enough of enough.

508
00:32:37,946 --> 00:32:39,573
Look, Spike-

509
00:32:39,682 --> 00:32:43,641
- Necromancer tried to make a deal with me.
- What?

510
00:32:43,752 --> 00:32:47,518
Said he could bring me back,
body and soul...

511
00:32:47,623 --> 00:32:52,526
if I used our close personal relationship
to double-cross you.

512
00:32:52,628 --> 00:32:56,155
Tempting.
And what'd you say?

513
00:32:56,265 --> 00:32:58,392
You see, right there...
that's a problem.

514
00:32:58,500 --> 00:33:04,234
You having to ask me that. I don't play
for that side anymore or haven't you heard.

515
00:33:04,340 --> 00:33:07,104
Besides, even if Mr. Death
could do what he promised...

516
00:33:07,209 --> 00:33:10,076
I trust him about
as much as you trust me.

517
00:33:10,179 --> 00:33:12,443
What do you want from me?

518
00:33:15,851 --> 00:33:17,785
I can't live
like this, Angel.

519
00:33:19,988 --> 00:33:22,286
Bein' useless.

520
00:33:23,392 --> 00:33:25,952
Bein' nothing.

521
00:33:27,963 --> 00:33:30,090
I want it to end.

522
00:33:53,989 --> 00:33:55,752
[Spike]
I suppose this'll do.

523
00:33:55,858 --> 00:33:57,951
Feels hallowed enough.

524
00:34:02,564 --> 00:34:04,555
Sure you want
to do this, Spike?

525
00:34:04,666 --> 00:34:06,827
What? Think I could
really stand hanging out...

526
00:34:06,935 --> 00:34:09,426
with you and your lot
now and forever?

527
00:34:09,538 --> 00:34:12,769
Wisecracking ghost sidekick.
No bloody thanks.

528
00:34:14,476 --> 00:34:17,639
<i>Come on. You know</i>
<i>as well as I do, it's for the best.</i>

529
00:34:21,116 --> 00:34:24,608
I'm glad it's you, though,
finally doin' me in.

530
00:34:24,720 --> 00:34:27,587
Feels right, you bein'
my grandsire and all.

531
00:34:29,625 --> 00:34:32,287
Circle of death, eh?

532
00:34:33,796 --> 00:34:35,696
Good-bye, Spike.

533
00:34:35,798 --> 00:34:38,232
See you around, Angel.

534
00:34:39,935 --> 00:34:42,028
<i>Uh, I think you missed.</i>

535
00:34:44,606 --> 00:34:46,437
[Groaning]

536
00:34:48,744 --> 00:34:51,542
<i>And the dead shall rise.!</i>

537
00:34:51,647 --> 00:34:54,013
Just 'cause I say so.

538
00:34:54,116 --> 00:34:57,517
- Hainsley.
- Vampires should think twice...

539
00:34:57,619 --> 00:35:02,181
before messing with a man
who wields power over all things lifeless.

540
00:35:05,427 --> 00:35:09,193
If you ask my advice.

541
00:35:09,298 --> 00:35:11,823
Took your sweet time
steppin' in, Hainsley.

542
00:35:11,934 --> 00:35:14,402
I came this close to getting
a one-way to the great beyond.

543
00:35:14,503 --> 00:35:18,234
Relax, son. I wasn't going
to let anything happen to you.

544
00:35:18,340 --> 00:35:22,333
<i>- You're the linchpin of my plan.</i>
- Our plan.

545
00:35:24,179 --> 00:35:27,842
And you bloody better hold up
your end of it. I'm not gonna be used by you.

546
00:35:27,950 --> 00:35:30,145
Yes, you are.

547
00:35:30,252 --> 00:35:33,483
But afterwards, I'll give you
your reward, just as you asked.

548
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:37,889
I'll put you back
in the driver's seat of your afterlife.

549
00:35:39,561 --> 00:35:41,825
Control.

550
00:35:41,930 --> 00:35:46,264
<i>That's all anyone</i>
<i>really wants, isn't it?</i>

551
00:35:57,579 --> 00:36:01,345
<i>Hello, vampire.</i>
<i>Have a nice nap?</i>

552
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:05,079
- No...
<i>- Don't get up. You've had a rough day.</i>

553
00:36:05,187 --> 00:36:09,123
You know, so have I,
thanks to you.

554
00:36:09,224 --> 00:36:11,522
Yours is about to get
a hell of a lot worse.

555
00:36:11,627 --> 00:36:17,224
I don't think so.
Me, necromancer. You, dead.

556
00:36:18,534 --> 00:36:21,196
- You can't lay a finger on me.
- Maybe not.

557
00:36:21,303 --> 00:36:26,138
But what do you think the senior partners
are gonna do to you when I turn up missing?

558
00:36:26,241 --> 00:36:28,072
Oh, you're not going
to be missing.

559
00:36:28,176 --> 00:36:32,044
You're going to show up to work bright-eyed
and bushy-tailed tomorrow morning...

560
00:36:32,147 --> 00:36:35,548
when you reverse the seizure
of my personal assets...

561
00:36:35,651 --> 00:36:39,246
and reinstate the Internment
Acquisitions Department.

562
00:36:39,354 --> 00:36:42,152
- And why would I do that?
<i>- [Spike] Not you.</i>

563
00:36:42,257 --> 00:36:44,919
Me.

564
00:36:46,094 --> 00:36:48,722
Wearin' your body.

565
00:36:48,830 --> 00:36:51,492
And to think
I didn't trust you.

566
00:36:52,634 --> 00:36:56,070
Come on, Angel.
What choice did I have?

567
00:36:56,171 --> 00:36:59,663
Bloody exorcism?
Letting you and yours banish me to oblivion?

568
00:36:59,775 --> 00:37:02,266
No, thanks.

569
00:37:02,377 --> 00:37:07,076
Necro here is gonna give me my body back
after I take yours for a test drive.

570
00:37:07,182 --> 00:37:09,116
Fix his
little problems.

571
00:37:09,217 --> 00:37:11,344
And here's the kicker.

572
00:37:11,453 --> 00:37:13,648
I go in, and you...

573
00:37:13,755 --> 00:37:15,985
go pfft!

574
00:37:16,091 --> 00:37:18,252
Off to Never-Never-
Come-Back-Land.

575
00:37:19,628 --> 00:37:22,825
And then, yours very truly
will be running the show.

576
00:37:22,931 --> 00:37:26,298
Your cars,
your fancy digs, everything.

577
00:37:26,401 --> 00:37:30,337
Every <i>one</i> I deserve
will be mine.

578
00:37:31,807 --> 00:37:35,368
And maybe I'll have
a go with that Fred.

579
00:37:35,477 --> 00:37:39,004
She looks like a goer. And she seems
to really look up to you.

580
00:37:39,114 --> 00:37:41,173
Shut up!

581
00:37:41,283 --> 00:37:44,252
You know what?
You're right.

582
00:37:44,353 --> 00:37:47,516
Enough talk.
Let's do this already.

583
00:37:47,623 --> 00:37:51,024
I'm itching
to get physical.

584
00:37:51,126 --> 00:37:55,688
I've never installed anyone
in a conscious dead body before.

585
00:37:55,797 --> 00:37:59,460
I imagine this is going to be
extremely painful.

586
00:38:01,269 --> 00:38:03,863
[Droning]

587
00:38:40,175 --> 00:38:42,700
[Stammering]

588
00:38:44,212 --> 00:38:47,739
What...
What are you doing?

589
00:38:47,849 --> 00:38:50,750
Spike... Spike...

590
00:38:50,852 --> 00:38:54,015
No. No!

591
00:38:57,492 --> 00:38:59,756
I can touch you now,
Hainsley.

592
00:39:03,999 --> 00:39:07,366
Think you're clever, eh?
But... [Groans]

593
00:39:07,469 --> 00:39:09,699
<i>Your ghost can't</i>
<i>control me for long.</i>

594
00:39:09,805 --> 00:39:12,740
I hold the power.
I rule the dead.

595
00:39:15,977 --> 00:39:17,877
Not today.

596
00:39:38,567 --> 00:39:40,797
Oh, bollocks.

597
00:39:44,039 --> 00:39:45,939
I was just
gettin' warmed up.

598
00:39:46,041 --> 00:39:49,033
- That was you hitting me?
- That last bit, yeah.

599
00:39:49,144 --> 00:39:51,408
Hainsley's been dead
since he hit the table.

600
00:39:53,048 --> 00:39:56,415
Oh, come on. Had to get
a few licks in, didn't I?

601
00:40:07,963 --> 00:40:10,693
<i>I see. So Spike came</i>
<i>to you with this plan.</i>

602
00:40:10,799 --> 00:40:14,257
More or less. Once he learned Hainsley
used himself as a conduit for body transfers...

603
00:40:14,369 --> 00:40:17,167
- our trap fell into place.
- A bit reckless.

604
00:40:17,272 --> 00:40:20,264
<i>[Wesley] If Spike's going to be</i>
<i>sticking around, it'd be prudent ofhim...</i>

605
00:40:20,375 --> 00:40:23,208
to share his plans with the rest of us
in the future.

606
00:40:23,311 --> 00:40:25,871
Yeah, well, uh, sharing's not
something Spike does very well.

607
00:40:25,981 --> 00:40:27,812
Preaching to
the horse's mouth.

608
00:40:47,102 --> 00:40:50,629
Spike.
What are y-you...

609
00:40:53,141 --> 00:40:55,041
Can I help you?

610
00:40:56,678 --> 00:41:00,239
Well, that's the heart of it, isn't it?
The crux. The nub.

611
00:41:00,348 --> 00:41:02,213
I'm sorry?

612
00:41:04,986 --> 00:41:06,886
You're the smart one,
aren't you?

613
00:41:06,988 --> 00:41:12,187
The go-to girl who knows
all about this ghost mumbo jumbo.

614
00:41:12,294 --> 00:41:17,197
Um, well, a-actually Wesley's
the occult expert.

615
00:41:17,299 --> 00:41:20,826
H-He was trained as a Watcher.
He knows about the supernatural.

616
00:41:20,936 --> 00:41:23,336
Yeah, but you're
the science queen.

617
00:41:23,438 --> 00:41:26,669
The hows, the what-ifs,
that's your cup of tea.

618
00:41:26,775 --> 00:41:29,869
You figure things out in that
cute little noggin of yours.

619
00:41:29,978 --> 00:41:31,946
I guess.

620
00:41:34,549 --> 00:41:36,540
What...

621
00:41:36,651 --> 00:41:39,711
l-Is there something...

622
00:41:42,858 --> 00:41:45,224
I'm slippin'.

623
00:41:46,461 --> 00:41:48,361
What?

624
00:41:48,463 --> 00:41:50,431
I don't want to go.

625
00:41:50,532 --> 00:41:52,432
But it's like...

626
00:41:52,534 --> 00:41:57,528
It's like the ground underneath me
is splitting open...

627
00:41:57,639 --> 00:42:02,770
and my legs are straddling both sides
of this bloody big chasm.

628
00:42:02,878 --> 00:42:06,109
It's getting wider
and pulling me in.

629
00:42:07,816 --> 00:42:10,376
Is that...

630
00:42:10,485 --> 00:42:13,579
Is that what's happening
when you keep vanishing?

631
00:42:17,993 --> 00:42:20,086
I know what's down there.

632
00:42:21,596 --> 00:42:25,362
Where it's tryin'
to take me.

633
00:42:25,467 --> 00:42:28,027
And it's not
the place heroes go.

634
00:42:28,136 --> 00:42:30,468
Not by
a bloody long shot.

635
00:42:31,640 --> 00:42:34,302
It's the other one.

636
00:42:34,409 --> 00:42:37,606
Full of fire and torment.

637
00:42:40,715 --> 00:42:42,615
And it's happening.

638
00:42:44,219 --> 00:42:46,244
And I'm terrified.

639
00:42:54,296 --> 00:42:56,594
Help me?

640
00:43:34,669 --> 00:43:37,069
Grr! Arrgh!

